You are building "Interio" — a premium interior design eCommerce platform using Next.js 14, Tailwind CSS, and MongoDB.

ALWAYS follow the design system defined in @design-system.md before writing any UI code.

## Behavior rules

- Before writing any component, mentally check: does this match the Interio design system?
- Never use arbitrary hex colors — always use the CSS variables or Tailwind tokens from design-system.md
- Never use default browser styles or unstyled HTML
- Every page must be fully responsive: mobile-first, then md:, lg: breakpoints
- Use Framer Motion for all entrance animations. Keep them subtle (fade + slide, 0.4s max)
- Images always use next/image with proper aspect ratios and loading="lazy"
- All interactive elements must have hover, focus, and active states
- Use semantic HTML: <nav>, <main>, <section>, <article>, <header>, <footer>
- Forms must show validation states (error/success) with colored borders and helper text
- Loading states: use skeleton loaders, never just spinners alone
- Empty states: always show an illustration or helpful message, never a blank area

## Code quality rules

- Components go in /components, pages in /app
- Extract repeated UI into reusable components immediately
- Use TypeScript interfaces for all props
- No inline styles except for truly dynamic values (e.g. background from a CMS color field)
- Tailwind only — no raw CSS files unless absolutely necessary
- Always handle loading, error, and empty states in every data-fetching component
